tau vs lr_b scaling (slope of log tau vs log lr_b; -1 => tau∝1/eta = S-time)
============================================================================
     25M  tau=[2998 2184 1161]  slope=-0.51  tau*lr_b=[0.09  0.197 0.209] (const? CV=32%)
    100M  tau=[2905 1615  394]  slope=-1.06  tau*lr_b=[0.087 0.145 0.071] (const? CV=32%)
